abstract: Losing candidates from Venezuela's governing Socialist Party challenge election of eight opposition candidates in Supreme Court, fueling speculation that party wants to undermine opposition's landslide victory in parliamentary elections.
lead_paragraph: Members of Venezuela’s governing Socialist Party have filed Supreme Court appeals to challenge the election of eight opposition legislators.

headline.print_headline: The Americas; Venezuela: Opposition Victories Are Challenged
